com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class Net

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Net
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Net>

    public class Net
extends Object
implements Comparable<Net>, Serializable
    This class represents the physical net to be routed (both inter-site and intra-site). It keeps track of site pins (both source and sinks) and routing resources used as PIPs. It also has references to keep track of the module it may be a part of.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • createPin

        public SitePinInst createPin(boolean isOutput,
                             String pinName,
                             SiteInst si)
        Convenience function that creates a new pin from the provided parameters and adds it to the net.

        Vivado Tcl:

        set p [create_pin -direction $isOutput $pinName]; connect_net -net $this $p

        Parameters:
        isOutput - Is the pin an output, true if is an output
        pinName - Name of the pin to create
        si - The site instance to which the newly created pin belongs
        Returns:
        The newly created pin if added successfully, null otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • addPIP

        public void addPIP(PIP pip)
        Adds a PIP to the net.

        Vivado Tcl:

        set r [get_property FIXED_ROUTE $this]; set p [get_pips_from $r]; set_property FIXED_ROUTE [lappend $r $p] $this

        Parameters:
        pip - The PIP to add.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • removePIP

        public boolean removePIP(PIP pip)
        Removes a PIP from the net.

        Vivado Tcl:

        set r [get_property FIXED_ROUTE $this]; set p [get_pips_from $r]; set i [lsearch $r $pip]; set r [lreplace $r $i $i]; set_property FIXED_ROUTE $r $this

        Parameters:
        pip - The PIP to remove.
        Returns:
        True if the operation completed successfully, false otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0
